This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it deals with the automatic temporal ordering of events described in discourse. It also involves the analysis of linguistic mechanisms used in text, which is a common area of research in NLP. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) as these fields are closely related to NLP. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves the extraction of temporal relations from text. Finally, Neural Networks (cs.NE) may also be a relevant sub-category as deep learning techniques are often used in NLP research.
